Commentary: fullish length around off stump, no swing and Fakhar punches in front of mid-off, pinches a single to get going
sliding across from over the wicket, towards the tramlines, again no movement and Babar accepts the freebie
goes fuller, 79mph on off and Babar slices one down to third man
pitched up in the corridor outside off, 82mph and Fakhar steps out to drill to the right of mid-off, just a single again
length ball, around middle and off, blocked back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Willey to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: what's this, chance of a run-out... Foakes misses from five yards away with Babar sprawling! It was a controlled punch into the covers, comfortable two but they then started for a third, Fakhar changed his mind and left Babar having to do a U-turn. But Foakes collected the throw in front of the wicket and somehow missed the stumps!
good length and prodded watchfully into the covers
Commentary_short: Willey to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: flayed through the covers for Pakistan first boundary! Sweet connection as Fakhar scythes through a full ball outside off
Commentary_short: Curran to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: fullish, room the free the hands again, this time he picks out cover
Commentary_short: Curran to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: pitched up again, 84mph and there's a sweeper out for the drive now
over the wicket to Babar, no slip in and he drops back to angle the ball wide of the keeper, just a cheeky late dab and it runs to the rope! First four for Babar
Commentary_short: Curran to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: straighter line, worked off the hip towards square leg

gottim, plucked above his head at cover! Maybe that was Curran's plan all along, just feed the drive... Fakhar was trying to hit that into the pavilion but mistimed the shot, still could have picked up four had Morgan not timed the jump right; had to go one-handed in the end but took it supremely well!
Dismissal_text: Fakhar Zaman c Morgan b Curran 7 (6b 1x4 0x6) SR: 116.66

Commentary: pitched up, 83mph and driven crisply but straight to extra cover
Commentary_short: Willey to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: shorter length, worked off the pads
length in the channel, softly played behind square
full on the pads and this is clipped in front of the sweeper at square leg for two
just a hint of wobble outside off, Babar dabs at it late and is beaten
Commentary_short: Willey to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: too full, in the slot, belted through the covers for four! That's a strong area for Babar - and he's not No. 1 in the world for nothing
Commentary_short: Willey to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: full of a length, 83mph and Imam decides to show his colours, lashes a straight drive but picks out mid-off
on the pads this time, but he can't work it past midwicket
touch shorter, angled across and Imam glides it off the back foot, goes quickly to backward point and there's no single on offer
again on the short side, 82mph outside off, dropped towards cover and the fielder races in
throws the hands at one and drags it through midwicket for on
slower ball from Curran, who then races down the wicket to field as Babar looks to his partner retreating to his ground at the non-striker's
Commentary_short: Curran to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: full from over the wicket, clipped off the pads behind square backwards square
full and straight again, clocking 90.8mph on the speed gun, worked in front of the square and they run well for two more
outside off, pitched up at 91mph, Imam chops down on it and they scamper through
length ball angling in on off, taking the pace off this time, 76mph and Babar waits for it to dab one to third man

dug in, Imam pulls but can only connect with the glove - and Archer strikes on debut! (Not for the first time this week.) Sharp bouncer, 88mph this time but it was enough to surprise Imam, and Archer is off and running, England trailing gooey-eyed in his wake!
short of a length on off stump, Haris shows it a straight bat in defence
Commentary_short: Archer to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: fired in straight, drifting leg side as it deflects off the pads... Jordan goes up in appeal, but umpire Gough isn't interested
Commentary_short: Jordan to Babar Azam, 1 leg bye

Commentary: dug in, room for Haris to have a swing outside off, gets it right off the toe and Archer gives it his all running from third man to try and spare his mate a boundary - in vain
Commentary_short: Jordan to Haris Sohail, FOUR runs

Commentary: full now, in the channel and Haris drive, hits Morgan in the covers
Commentary_short: Jordan to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: good length, 85mph and this is jabbed with an open face to backward point
Commentary_short: Jordan to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: takes the pace off this time, pushed square but Duckett is across to field this time
Commentary_short: Jordan to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: another slowie, 70mph and clipped off the pads, picks up a couple behind square
tossed up nice and full on middle and off, Babar drives it back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Rashid to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: wide of off stump, possible a googly and it's whipped through midwicket coming forwards
advances down, smashes this to... well, only about halfway to long-on. Came off the toe of the bat, there was a man coming in but he had no chance of getting to the catch
floated up and tapped to leg
Commentary_short: Rashid to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: flicks the googly away behind square for one more
flighted and worked with the spin for another single - tidy first over from Rashid
Jordan hits a good length on off stump, 84mph and Haris blocks
Commentary_short: Jordan to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: offcutter, Haris goes big and this time gets it out of somewhere neat the middle of the bat! Only just clears the short boundary at deep midwicket, Willey gamely jumped for it one-handed but no dice - first six of the innings
Commentary_short: Jordan to Haris Sohail, SIX runs

Commentary: pushed across the left-hander, who plays at it and misses
Commentary_short: Jordan to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: fired well wide of the off stump, making Haris go to the longer boundary... but he reaches out and slaps this firmly behind backward point, Denly's dive in vain
Commentary_short: Jordan to Haris Sohail, FOUR runs

Commentary: fullish on the pads and clipped for a single
bit of width, 85mph and Babar uses that to his advantage to larrup a cut through backward point for four more - 15 off the over and that's a timely bump for the Pakistan run rate
Commentary_short: Jordan to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: tossed up and worked off the pads
Babar's on dance floor, raising the roof with a lofted drive into the stands! Sweetly struck and they're taking cover in the crowd at long-on!
Commentary_short: Rashid to Babar Azam, SIX runs

Commentary: pushed through and whipped to leg
slips in a googly, Haris waits and clips off his pads
flighted, Babar comes down again and punches through mid-on
another wrong'un, steered away through point playing back
length ball, slower delivery and Haris nurdles to leg, there's a misfield running in and they come back for a second
width and Haris throws the hands, 86mph delivery and a thick edge travels lickety-split to the rope at third man!
Commentary_short: Archer to Haris Sohail, FOUR runs

Commentary: zips this one through, slightly short and Haris looks to make room, can't lay bat on ball
Commentary_short: Archer to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: round the wicket, 91.2mph on the stumps, calmly worked into the gap between deep midwicket and long-on

ooh, streaky! Foakes flings himself to his left and can't quite get there! Backing away, Haris dabs and gets a thick edge but with Foakes going down the leg side he has to adjust... and can only get fingertips on it!
Commentary_short: Archer to Haris Sohail, FOUR runs

Commentary: pitched up and punched into the off side
sliding on, another googly to the left-hander, squeezed into the off side
bat and pad together as the batsman gallops down the pitch to negate the spin, a bit of an appeal but he was so far down
Commentary_short: Rashid to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: once again, way down the pitch at the point of impact ... Morgan thinks of the review as the ball deflects to the off side, but no
Commentary_short: Rashid to Babar Azam, 1 leg bye

Commentary: back in the crease this time, eased into the covers
dragged down, hauled out to the leg side, that's a loose one from Rashid, and punished with a rollicking pull
Commentary_short: Rashid to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: nurdled to wide long-on, a decent finish to a previously tight over
back of a length, a bit of width, dabbed to deep point
opens the face, glides a cut to backward point
banged in short, Babar ducks
Commentary_short: Curran to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: tip and run, into the off side, sharp single as mid-off swoops
rolls the fingers, a dab to the leg side, picking the slower ball, they turn for a tight second, but the throw is wayward
very full, in the slot for a slog, but instead pressed very firmly to mid-off, who gathers on the bounce
Commentary_short: Curran to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: a slow-turning pie! Like a tin of Fray Bentos in the microwave, pongo-ed up and over midwicket!
Commentary_short: Denly to Babar Azam, SIX runs

Commentary: oops, another half-tracking honker, absolutely leathered over cow corner! Get those fingers warm, Joe!
Commentary_short: Denly to Babar Azam, SIX runs

Commentary: better length, tucked to the leg side, and up comes a 31-ball fifty for the world's No.1 T20I batsman
flashed to deep cover, another easy single
fuller, straighter, pressed to cover
Commentary_short: Denly to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: tossed up on a better length, Denly clawed that back well, as Babar settles for a measured push to cover
banged into the ribs, pulled calmly round the corner
short again, well directed, thudding into a mistimed pull as Babar loses sight of it
outside off, unlucky for Willey, Haris was retreating to leg so it was the right idea
line and length, bursting past a wild mow. A valuable dot
Commentary_short: Willey to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: retreats to leg, opens the face on a full length, stabbed down to third man. Well played and placed
wide line, attacking the tramlines, and that was marginal but correct
outside off once more, stabbed to point as Haris chooses to chase it. Had he left it alone, it would have been another wide
Commentary_short: Willey to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: flashed in the air, up and over backward point! Willey aims fuller, but Haris is alert to the line now, and chops uppishly, loads of bottom hand, skewing the cut away through the field
Commentary_short: Willey to Haris Sohail, FOUR runs

Commentary: chopped into the covers
loops in the yorker, dabbed out to deep cover, and Haris joins Babar on fifty. Pakistan are cooking!
slammed on the up, and over the covers! It's an outswinging half-volley, picked early and panned to the rope, with an open face to beat the field. Lovely tonking
Commentary_short: Curran to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: yawned into the leg side, Jordan pounces with intent on the boundary's edge
slower ball, looped onto a good length, well played but more or less picked, rolling out to no-man's land at deep midwicket
back of a length, cutter, chopped to cover
slower ball, angled into the top of the stumps, calmly deflected through third man
spears in the yorker from round the wicket, excellent delivery, squirted to point
Commentary_short: Archer to Haris Sohail, no run

Commentary: hauled out to deep midwicket, but that's the slower ball, banged into the pitch, and Haris hasn't got hold of it! Willey steadies himself on the edge of the rope, and that's another vital scalp from Archer!
Dismissal_text: Haris Sohail c Willey b Archer 50 (36b 5x4 1x6) SR: 138.88

Commentary: hopping across the stumps to a full length, flicked to the leg side
Commentary_short: Archer to Asif Ali, 1 leg bye

Commentary: two wickets in the over! And though this won't count as Archer's wicket, he's made it happen. Chasing down the leg-side flick in his followthrough, gathering well, with two stumps to aim at, and pinging down Babar's timbers as he strove to make his ground!
pumped into the covers, excellent timing to end a superb innings-changing over
slower ball, outside off, dabbed to point
outside off, chopped to third man
slower ball again, so slow it barely reaches the batsman, let alone bouncing high enough to connect with his ambitious slap across the line
Commentary_short: Jordan to Imad Wasim, no run

Commentary: spanked back to the bowler, dropped, one-handed in a reflexive leap! Nearly caught on the rebound too, but instead gathered with the non-striker ambling out of his crease, and under-armed into the stumps!
clocked into the covers
another slower ball, tight line on off stump, tapped to cover
right up to the toes, clipped firmly to midwicket, and another mix-up between the wickets. Careful now!
outside off, zipping through to the keeper from round the wicket. Lovely change of pace, proper wheels on that one
Commentary_short: Archer to Imad Wasim, no run

Commentary: very full and straight, thumped with intent to mid-on
flipped to the leg side, timed it well, using the pace and the slight error in direction
Commentary_short: Archer to Faheem Ashraf, FOUR runs

Commentary: yorker, lovely length, can't do much with that, except not get out
turns his stance inside-out, can't connect with a flick over the leg side. Another fine over from Archer, whose spell has made the difference so far
Commentary_short: Archer to Imad Wasim, no run

Commentary: reverse-slap, can't connect properly
pounded hard back over the bowler's head! That's a proper wallop
Commentary_short: Rashid to Imad Wasim, FOUR runs

Commentary: flatter googly, can't get this one away
another googly, Faheem opens his stance, but can't get it away properly, through point
a smear across the line, this is a fine over in the circumstances
tossed up on the legs, flogged to deep midwicket, Rash's day is done
good pace, banged into the hip, and Imad can't connect on the pull
right up to the blockhole, flashed back to the bowler and dropped! Though, intercepted is probably fairer. He stuck out a mitt and stopped the run
attempted yorker, and that is utterly flogged on the up over long-off! Picked the length early, right underneath the shot with oodles of lovely bottom hand. Like a left-handed Jos Buttler
Commentary_short: Jordan to Faheem Ashraf, SIX runs

Commentary: clears the front foot, smashed high and hard, but straight to Denly at deep cover! Easy as pie, and Pakistan's momentum is stymied again
Dismissal_text: Faheem Ashraf c Denly b Jordan 17 (10b 1x4 1x6) SR: 170.00

Commentary: very full again, and thumped off the toe of the bat, straight through long-off! Placement over timing, and valuable runs!
Commentary_short: Jordan to Imad Wasim, FOUR runs

Commentary: supreme finish! Whipped with brutal wrists, clean past the sweeper at fine leg! Offline from Jordan, and punished behind square. That's a much healthier total than appeared likely after their wobble.
Commentary_short: Jordan to Imad Wasim, FOUR runs

Commentary: fired in and drifting into the pads from round the wicket, Vince flicks and it comes off the pad behind square
stays round the wicket to the left-hander, floated up outside off and drilled to long-off... they scamper through for one more
quick and on the stumps, Vince takes a step and punches down the ground
pushes across, a touch wide and Duckett opens up to clout towards extra cover - well stopped on the dive
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Duckett, no run

Commentary: darted on the stumps again, clipped off the front pad and midwicket is a touch deep
pushed through on middle and leg, Vince clips this regally into the leg side, finds a big gap in front of deep square leg, they hustle back for three
touch short and wide, Vince doesn't move his feet and swishes outside off, fails to connect
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Vince, no run

Commentary: presses out and taps this into the covers
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Vince, no run

Commentary: smashed off a length, that's flown hard and flat over long-on! About as agricultural as Vince gets, but that was belted out of the middle of the bat
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Vince, SIX runs

Commentary: turned off the pads into the leg side
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Vince, no run

Commentary: short, 84mph and it sits outside off, Vince roundhouses a pull straight down the ground, long-on is in place now
shortish, not much room but he plays late and opens the face to steer a couple in front of backward point
full and wide, Duckett doesn't need a sighter, hands flowing through a cover drive that leaves the fielder in the dirt! Comes on quick, leaves even quicker
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Duckett, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower ball, 78mph and tucked to the leg side
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Duckett, no run

Commentary: pitched up, 86mph outside off, Duckett creams it in the air - bagged at mid-off! Sheehan pulls out the Star Man pose, living up to his namesake Shahid! Struck it pretty well, maybe off the toe, but Duckett won't trouble the scorers any longer on T20I debut
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Duckett, OUT
Dismissal_text: BM Duckett c Imad Wasim b Shaheen Shah Afridi 9 (7b 1x4 0x6) SR: 128.57

Commentary: stays over the wicket, fullish and driven along the carpet to point
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Root, no run

Commentary: short ball down the leg side, Root pulls at it and Sarfrarz goes up in appeal.... Alex Wharf signals wide
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Root, 1 wide

Commentary: on the strumps, 88.7mph and Root deftly manoeuvres it through square leg to get off the mark
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Root, 1 run

Commentary: full and straight and clipped back down the pitch
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Vince, 1 run

Commentary: dug in short and Vince rolls his wrists on a flat pull to deep square
back of a length outside off, 87mph and Root stays back and rides it
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Root, no run

Commentary: full and fast, low-sling and swerving in as Root wristily flicks the ball away for one
full and a touch wide, 86mph and punched square to the man at point
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Vince, no run

Commentary: short ball, taking the pace off and it loops up out of reach of Vince, that'll be a wide on height
pitched up, just 76mph and Vince has to reach in front of himself, picks out extra cover
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Vince, no run

Commentary: goes for the full bunger but that's a gimme, crunched past the infield to the cover-point boundary for four
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Vince, FOUR runs

Commentary: skiddy, short of a length, 84mph/136kph and Root fends it short fine leg
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Root, no run

Commentary: dug in, room outside off for Root to guide a cut down to third man for one
back of a length, Vince chops off the back foot without timing
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Vince, no run

Commentary: takes the pace off, Vince baseball-bats down the pitch, direct hit from Hasan after fielding in his follow-through... But Vince had grounded his bat and they steal one
shortish and dabbed behind point off the back foot
shortish and a touch wide, 86mph/139kph and cracked behind point with princely timing to pick up four more
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Vince, FOUR runs

Commentary: banged in, 85mph outside off and tapped square
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Root, no run

Commentary: short and on the hips, Root swivels and swats behind square on the leg side, they come back for two
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Root, 2 runs

Commentary: on the pads and worked into the gap at backward square once again
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Root, 2 runs

Commentary: drops into the crease and opens the face to guide one into the off side
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Root, 1 run

Commentary: Vince comes out, slower ball from Shaheen going round the wicket, checked to mid-off
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Vince, 1 run

Commentary: short and sliding leg side, nicely paddled around the corner and it beats short fine leg to skip away
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Root, FOUR runs

Commentary: darted in on the stumps and Vince works towards midwicket
straight line, pushed through quickly and clipped off the legs again
tossed up and driven down the ground
Root takes a step and Imad fires it wide, punched through the covers for one
flat and punched off off stump back past the bowler
pushed through again, nagging away on off stump, no width to work with and Root chops to point
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Root, no run

Commentary: pitched up around the line of off, Vince opens up and stabs through point
the young shaver hurtles in and bounces Root at 88mph, pulled down into the ground for one to fine leg
slower ball, but basically a wide half-tracker and Vince hammers a drive away from his body through cover, gives the sweeper no chance
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Vince, FOUR runs

Commentary: straighter and clipped to leg, Imam pounces to prevent more than a single
fuller on middle and leg, Root pushes to mid-on
full of a length, 88mph and driven square from off stump, flies low to backward point and they don't risk it
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Vince, no run

Commentary: flat on the stumps, into the pads but probably sliding down
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Root, no run

Commentary: lobbed up outside off, Root makes room to drive inside to out
Vince opens the shoulders and hits down the ground, just a single there
flighted, outside leg and Root paddles it past the keeper
worked into the leg side, a misfield gives Vince a second

drifting leg side again, Vince overbalances playing across the line, half a chance of a stumping... But Pakistan think there was an edge and Wharf's finger goes up! Vince, though, looks bemused and calls for a review. What does Ultra Edge say? There's something on the graph, a thin spike as ball passed bat - and that's enough for Tim Robinson! Vince looks forlorn as he walks off, maybe thinking he hit the ground, but again he fails to convert a good start

Commentary: short of a length, pulled fine for one
back of a length, 88mph and Morgan swats it away for his first run
short of a length, Root fails to connect with a pull - the ball then rebounds up out of the gloves to hit Sarfaraz in the hooter. Owee!
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Root, no run

Commentary: length ball clipped off the pads and they think about a third, settle for two
dug in, 86mph and Root plays a controlled pull in front of square
banged in at Morgan's bonce, he takes the short ball on and heaves it away towards fine leg, first boundary for the captain
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Morgan, FOUR runs

Commentary: ooh, cheeky from Root! Inverses his stance, gets right underneath the off-stump delivery, and scoops it over the keeper's head
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Root, FOUR runs

Commentary: back and across, looking to make room on the off side but can't make proper contact
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Root, no run

Commentary: punched up to long off for the single
biffed out through extra cover, meeting the low full toss with a big stride outside off
right behind the line, pressed back up the pitch
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Morgan, no run

Commentary: clonked onto the on-side, Imad's fine spell is through
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Morgan, no run

Commentary: speared into the pads on a full length, Root should have clipped that mercilessly through fine leg, but settles for the deflection off the legs
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Root, 1 leg bye

Commentary: very full, angling away from the left-hander, Morgan slaps an air-shot
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Morgan, no run

Commentary: spanked high and not entirely mighty! Wafting through the line, right under the stroke, but Hasan and Shaheen can't decide who should go for the chance, and it plops inches over the long at long-off!

Commentary: flogged with pre-emptive disdain through the leg side. Big over brewing ...
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Morgan, FOUR runs

Commentary: a bottom-handed battering ram! All in the wrists, as Morgan meets the full length with a free-flowing yahoo over the covers!
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Morgan, FOUR runs

Commentary: hauled out to the leg side, he was swinging for the hills once again, and a better connection would have vanished into the Taff. Instead, it was inside-edged through square leg
full toss, very straight, which was all that was going for it. Root is too surprised to take full advantage, and cloths a slog to midwicket. Up comes the hundred
wicket-to-wicket,  but pitching outside leg as the ball skitters through to short third man off the knee-roll
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Morgan, 1 leg bye

Commentary: yorker, very full, well dug out
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Root, no run

Commentary: full once more, Root can't do much but defend this again, just a hint of swing on offer too ...
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Root, no run

Commentary: this is tremendous bowling! Tailing in, yorker length, 91mph, Root is flat-footed as he stabs his bat down late and barely connects
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Root, no run

Commentary: tremendous riposte! Out comes the sweep, and he's nailed it! Plumb lbw if he misses that, instead it's clean through fine leg.
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Root, FOUR runs

Commentary: half-forward to the full length, angled in to the left-hander
down the track, mowing across the line, Root connects, but not especially well. Out through midwicket
good solid biff to mid-off, didn't nail the yorker but got away with it
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Morgan, no run

Commentary: back of a length, banged into the deck, and pulled calmly to the leg side. This has been a fine over so far
very full, and elegantly eased through long-off! Root just swapped his bat, and he's clearly picked a perfect one!
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Root, FOUR runs

Commentary: short, swivelled out to deep midwicket, another single as Root keeps the strike.
down on one knee, lovely contact! Eye on the ball all the way, meeting it on the full and deflecting to perfection through fine leg
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Root, FOUR runs

Commentary: yorker, well directed, but flicked to the leg side
back and across, and dabbed to the off side for the cheeky single
charging out of his crease, and rather shocked by the full-bunger. A cramped pull at 88mph to midwicket. A glance at the umpire, but had he been back in the crease that wouldn't be above waist-height
flicked off the hip to midwicket again
very full, Pakistan are nailing their yorkers right now, and England aren't quite getting the rate they need, but they are keeping in touch
tailing in once more, deflected behind square
hoisted out to deep midwicket! Lovely pick-up from outside off, and it's utterly clobbered that over the leg side boundary. It's an over-step too, so a free hit coming up...
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Morgan, (no ball) SIX runs

Commentary: very well bowled in the circumstances, another yorker, thumped on the up to long-on
scooped straight to Sarfraz! Looking to get the elevation over the keeper's head, but was suckered by the cutter, and feathered a thin edge to the keeper. A decent knock, but a timely breakthrough!

Commentary: chipped on the up, but short of long-on

banged in short, pulled with intent behind square, and Haris makes an utter mess of that one, attempting to scoop in one hand, he instead fell over his own feet, and pulled down his own pants as the ball rolled into the rope!
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Morgan, FOUR runs

Commentary: hauled out to backward square leg. England keeping themselves in touch now
tight line, attacking the top of off, dabbed to third man
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morgan, 1 run

Commentary: good scampering from Denly, beating the shy from mid-off
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Denly, 1 run

Commentary: short, too short, launching high over the batsman's head
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morgan, 1 wide

Commentary: flogged to deep point, another single
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morgan, 1 run

Commentary: right up to the toes, flicked to midwicket, a fumble, thoughts of a single, the throw goes wide, a lot of drama for not a lot
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Denly, no run

Commentary: very full, outswinging yorker, this is quality containment. Can't do much with that
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Denly, no run

Commentary: low full toss, but this time Denly's drive pierces the field! Deeper in the crease this time, giving himself leverage, and filleting a vital boundary
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Denly, FOUR runs

Commentary: full toss, a slap over the head of mid-off! Morgan got that one very high on the bat, but got enough on the shot to inflict the damage
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Morgan, FOUR runs

Commentary: boshed out to cover
back of a length, a slower ball, Denly dabs to cover and a quick single
round the wicket, cramping for room, eased to the leg side
an insolent swipe, and an under-edge through fine leg!
Commentary_short: Hasan Ali to Denly, FOUR runs

Commentary: wafted across the line, Denly keeps the strike. England are in command
in the slot, on the toes, and Denly launches this one flat over wide long-on! Superb contact, and it's down to a run a ball now
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Denly, SIX runs

Commentary: yorker again, Pakistan have bowled them well, stabbed to the leg side
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Denly, 1 run

Commentary: very full, tailing in, stabbed out to the off side
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morgan, 1 run

Commentary: full once more, flogged through the leg side again to keep the requirement draining away
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Denly, 1 run

Commentary: full toss, smacked to long-on
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morgan, 1 run

Commentary: crashed to cover, Denly wanted the single but Morgan sends him back! Safe in the end, Morgan wanted the strike for the final over
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Denly, no run

Commentary: a hint of width, nailed out to the sweeper in the covers, Morgan's back for the second to bring up his fifty. Job almost done
sealed with a six! Spanked high over long-off! And Morgan is seriously pumped about that win, toppling the No.1 T20 team in the world is no mean feat, and he's done it in style!
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Morgan, SIX runs
